I once saw someone playing this against a lifegain deck. His opponent went from 120 to 10 to 0 life in one turn. It was beautiful.  

@Darthparralax: Do you really think that [Sorin, Lord of Innistrad](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sorin, Lord of Innistrad) + [Doubling Season](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doubling Season) will be broken enough to be banned everywhere? I kind of highly doubt it.  
And if someone manages to assemble Sorin + Doubling Season + [Experiment kraj](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Experiment kraj) + [Mycosynth Lattice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mycosynth Lattice) + [March of the Machines](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=March of the Machines) / [Tezzeret, Agent of Bolas](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tezzeret, Agent of Bolas) combo (4 colors, 5 cards, CMCs 4-6), that person deserves to win anyway.
